      </div>

      <p class="lead">Creative coding transforms algorithms into art, numbers into beauty, and logic into emotion. It's a practice that sits at the intersection of programming and visual design, where mathematical concepts become the brush strokes of digital artists.</p>

      <p>This field has exploded in recent years as artists, designers, and developers discover the expressive power of code. From simple geometric patterns to complex generative systems, creative coding opens up new possibilities for artistic expression that would be impossible with traditional tools.</p>

      <h2>The Language of Mathematics</h2>

      <p>At its heart, creative coding is about translating mathematical concepts into visual experiences. Sine waves become flowing animations, fractals create intricate organic patterns, and random numbers introduce delightful unpredictability.</p>

      <div class="code-visual-pair">
        <div class="code-block">
          <h3>Perlin Noise Pattern</h3>
          <pre><code>function draw() {
  for (let x = 0; x < width; x += 10) {
    for (let y = 0; y < height; y += 10) {
      let noiseVal = noise(x * 0.01, y * 0.01, frameCount * 0.01);
      let hue = map(noiseVal, 0, 1, 0, 360);
      fill(hue, 80, 90);
      circle(x, y, noiseVal * 20);
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="visual-result">
          <div class="noise-demo" id="noise-canvas"></div>
          <p class="demo-caption">Live visualization of the Perlin noise algorithm</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The beauty of this approach is that small changes in the code can produce dramatically different visual results. Adjusting a single parameter can transform flowing organic shapes into rigid geometric patterns, or change a gentle animation into chaotic motion.</p>

