        "Creative coding isn't about replacing traditional art‚Äîit's about expanding the palette of human expression to include the infinite possibilities of computation."
        <cite>‚Äî Casey Reas, Co-creator of Processing</cite>
      </blockquote>

      <h2>Interactive Installations</h2>

      <p>One of the most exciting applications of creative coding is in interactive installations that respond to human presence and movement. These pieces blur the line between observer and participant, creating unique experiences for each viewer.</p>

