                <option value="monochrome">Monochrome</option>
                <option value="warm">Warm Tones</option>
                <option value="cool">Cool Tones</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <button id="regenerate" class="generate-btn">Generate New Pattern</button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="generator-output">
          <canvas id="generative-canvas" width="400" height="300"></canvas>
          <p class="output-caption">Real-time generative art based on your preferences</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The fascinating aspect of generative systems is their capacity for emergence‚Äîcomplex, beautiful patterns arising from simple rules. This mirrors natural processes and creates connections between digital art and biological systems.</p>

      <h2>Shader Programming</h2>

      <p>Shaders are programs that run on the graphics card, allowing for incredibly complex visual effects that render in real-time. They're the secret behind much of modern creative coding's visual sophistication.</p>

      <div class="shader-example">
        <div class="shader-code">
          <h3>Fragment Shader</h3>
          <pre><code>uniform float time;
uniform vec2 resolution;

void main() {
    vec2 uv = gl_FragCoord.xy / resolution.xy;
    vec2 center = vec2(0.5, 0.5);
    float dist = distance(uv, center);
    
    float wave = sin(dist * 20.0 - time * 3.0) * 0.5 + 0.5;
    vec3 color = vec3(wave * uv.x, wave * uv.y, wave);
    
    gl_FragColor = vec4(color, 1.0);
}</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="shader-result">
          <div class="shader-demo" id="shader-canvas"></div>
          <p class="demo-caption">GPU-powered visual effects running at 60fps</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>Shader programming opens up possibilities for real-time effects that would be computationally impossible with traditional CPU-based approaches. Complex lighting, fluid simulations, and intricate pattern generation all become feasible.</p>

